Demonstration of hvector derived datatype

hvector is the same as vector except that it takes stride in bytes rather than
counts, i.e., stride is the number of bytes between start of each block. It can
be calculated as blocklength times extent.

    int MPI_Type_create_hvector(int count, int blocklength, MPI_Aint stride,
                                MPI_Datatype oldtype, MPI_Datatype *newtype)
